--> What is FinStack
A modular ERP system for Indian SMEs to manage sales, inventory, accounting, and GST compliance with 
a double-entry accounting engine.

--> Tech
Node.js + Express вҖ” Backend API server
TypeScript вҖ” Type safety across frontend and backend
PostgreSQL вҖ” Relational integrity for double-entry accounting
Prisma вҖ” it gives you type-safe database queries and handles migrations so your schema is version controlled.
JWT вҖ” Authentication
Swagger вҖ” API documentation


--> Module Architecture
Purchase Module
  - depends on: Accounting Engine, GST Calculator, Inventory
  - owns: purchase_orders, purchase_invoices, purchase_invoice_items, purchase_returns

Sales Module
  - depends on: Accounting Engine, GST Calculator, Inventory
  - owns: sales_orders, sales_invoices, sales_invoice_items, sales_returns

Expense Module
  - depends on: Accounting Engine, GST Calculator
  - owns: expense_vouchers

Accounting Module (THE ENGINE)
  - depends on: NOTHING
  - owns: vouchers, ledger_entries, ledger_accounts, financial_years

Ledger Module
  - depends on: Accounting Module (reads from ledger_entries)
  - owns: no extra tables, it reads from accounting tables

Inventory Module
  - depends on: NOTHING
  - owns: items, item_categories, stock_movements, warehouses

GST Module
  - depends on: NOTHING (it's a calculator, it reads config and computes)
  - owns: hsn_sac_codes, gst_config

P&L / Reports Module
  - depends on: Accounting Module (reads ledger_entries and aggregates)
  - owns: no tables, it's pure read-only queries


